1. PH2 contions XCK2 (External clock of USART2), and if XCK is used as gpio it disables the timer4 whose OCR's are on PORTH
2. PS2 debouncing has been solved using botton released technique i.e keep setting a flag till the button is released and monitor that flag.
3. To stop erasing eeprom during buring a uC set the EESAVE fuse bit.
4. If a while condition contains && then if condition contains || to check if loop has breaked and vice versa.
5. To detect if a sensor has given stable vales use 2 variables which will store an initial value and a variable which will store 2nd value (use a flag here for storing )  
